<subSubSection id="12E932B9FFAF98310197ADFA701EFBD0" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5A4C6132FFAF98310197ADFA701EFBD0" blockId="15.[151,1437,351,1026]" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF98310197ADFA721EFE10" bold="true" box="[199,315,423,449]" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="9DF31AB1FFAF98310012ADFA7145FE10" baseAuthorityName="Shcherbak" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[322,608,423,449]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Cosmolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lutegiensis">
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF98310012ADFA7145FE10" box="[322,608,423,449]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">Cosmolaelaps lutegiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<collectingRegion id="9837AFD0FFAF9831021BADFA70A7FE10" box="[843,898,423,449]" country="Ukraine" name="Kyiv" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">Kiev</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="22E421A2FFAF983102DEADFA70CDFE10" box="[910,1000,423,449]" name="Ukraine" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="3E621CC3FFAF983102A7ADFA77E3FE10" author="Shcherbak, G. I." box="[1015,1222,423,449]" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" pagination="76 - 79" refId="ref16468" refString="Shcherbak, G. I. (1971 a) New species of gamasid from the genus Hypoaspis Canestrini (Acarina, Gamasoidea). Vestnik Zoologii, 5, 76 - 79. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1971">Shcherbak, 1971a</bibRefCitation>
). It has been found from soil-litter of a pine forest and is now recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="22E421A2FFAF9831025FAD96707FFE34" box="[783,858,459,485]" name="Russia" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">Russia</collectingCountry>
for the first time, from the soil. Our newly collected material agrees very well with the description given by 
<bibRefCitation id="3E621CC3FFAF9831024DADB270DDFDD8" author="Shcherbak, G. I." box="[797,1016,495,521]" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" pagination="76 - 79" refId="ref16468" refString="Shcherbak, G. I. (1971 a) New species of gamasid from the genus Hypoaspis Canestrini (Acarina, Gamasoidea). Vestnik Zoologii, 5, 76 - 79. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1971">Shcherbak (1971a)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="3E621CC3FFAF98310555ADB27635FDD8" author="Ramroodi, S. &amp; Hajizadeh, J. &amp; Joharchi, O." box="[1029,1296,495,522]" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" pagination="533 - 544" refId="ref16273" refString="Ramroodi, S., Hajizadeh, J. &amp; Joharchi, O. (2014) Two new species of Cosmolaelaps Berlese (Acari: Laelapidae) from Iran. Zootaxa, 3847 (4), 533 - 544. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3847.4.3" type="journal article" year="2014">
Ramroodi 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF9831052FADAD7797FDD8" box="[1151,1202,495,521]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">et al</emphasis>
. (2014)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="3E621CC3FFAF9831044EADB2720FFDFC" author="Joharchi, O &amp; Trach, V. A." pageId="15" pageNumber="501" pagination="486 - 494" refId="ref14677" refString="Joharchi, O &amp; Trach, V. A. (2019) A new species of Cosmolaelaps Berlese (Acari: Laelapidae) from Ukraine. Zootaxa, 4647 (1), 486 - 494. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4647.1.30" type="journal article" year="2019">Joharchi &amp; Trach (2019)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="3E621CC3FFAF98310033AE4E717EFDFC" author="Joharchi, O. &amp; Issakova, A. K. &amp; Asyamova, O. S. &amp; Abbasi-Sarcheshmeh, M. &amp; Tolstikov, A. V." box="[355,603,531,558]" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" pagination="473 - 498" refId="ref14853" refString="Joharchi, O., Issakova, A. K., Asyamova, O. S., Abbasi-Sarcheshmeh, M. &amp; Tolstikov, A. V. (2020 a) Some soil-inhabiting mites (Acari: Mesostigmata) from Kazakhstan, with description of a new species of Gaeolaelaps Evans &amp; Till (Acari: Laelapidae). Zootaxa, 4819 (3), 473 - 498. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4819.3.3" type="journal article" year="2020">
Joharchi 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF98310097AE4972D2FDFC" box="[455,503,531,557]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">et al</emphasis>
. (2020a)
</bibRefCitation>
have reported the species from 
<collectingCountry id="22E421A2FFAF983102E9AE4970CCFDFF" box="[953,1001,532,558]" name="Iran" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">Iran</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="22E421A2FFAF983102A2AE4E7769FDFC" box="[1010,1100,531,557]" name="Ukraine" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="22E421A2FFAF983105D0AE4E7623FDFC" box="[1152,1286,531,557]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, respectively. They stated inaccurately that the dorsal shield has 38 pairs of lancet-like setae, but there are 39 pairs (including two pairs of 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF98310073AE01721AFDA4" box="[291,319,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">Zx</emphasis>
setae between 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF983100B8AE0172D1FDA4" box="[488,500,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">J</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF9831037BAE01711EFDA4" box="[555,571,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">Z</emphasis>
setae, and three unpaired setae 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF983102CCAE017090FDA4" box="[924,949,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">Jx</emphasis>
between 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF9831054FAE06771FFDA4" box="[1055,1082,603,629]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">J3</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF9831053FAE0177AFFDA7" box="[1135,1162,604,630]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">J5</emphasis>
) as stated in the original description (see 
<bibRefCitation id="3E621CC3FFAF9831001DAE22713DFD48" author="Shcherbak, G. I." box="[333,536,639,665]" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" pagination="76 - 79" refId="ref16468" refString="Shcherbak, G. I. (1971 a) New species of gamasid from the genus Hypoaspis Canestrini (Acarina, Gamasoidea). Vestnik Zoologii, 5, 76 - 79. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1971">Shcherbak, 1971a</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="3E621CC3FFAF9831037BAEDD71CBFD48" author="Bregetova, N. G." box="[555,750,639,666]" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" pagination="483 - 554" refId="ref13808" refString="Bregetova, N. G. (1977) Family Laelaptidae Berlese, 1892. In: Ghilyarov, M. S. &amp; Bregetova, N. G. (Eds.) Key to the Soil Inhabiting Mites. Mesostigmata. Nauka, Leningrad, pp. 483 - 554. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1977">Bregetova (1977)</bibRefCitation>
suspected 
<taxonomicName id="9DF31AB1FFAF98310237AE2277A1FD48" baseAuthorityName="Shcherbak" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[871,1156,639,665]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Cosmolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lutegiensis">
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF98310237AE2277A1FD48" box="[871,1156,639,665]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">Cosmolaelaps lutegiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
maybe a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="9DF31AB1FFAF983101E6AEF972DCFD6F" authority="Samsinak, 1958" authorityName="Samsinak" authorityYear="1958" box="[182,505,675,702]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Hypoaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helianthi">
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF983101E6AEF973EFFD6C" box="[182,202,676,701]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF98310188AEFE7219FD6C" box="[216,316,675,701]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">helianthi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3E621CC3FFAF98310013AEFE72DCFD6F" author="Samsinak, K." box="[323,505,675,702]" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" pagination="185 - 198" refId="ref16440" refString="Samsinak, K. (1958) Roztoci ze slunecnicovych semen (Acari). Ceskoslovenska Parasitologie, 5, 185 - 198. [in Czech]" type="journal article" year="1958">Samšiňák, 1958</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. We have not had the opportunity to examine the 
<typeStatus id="8548DF90FFAF98310577AEF97772FD6F" box="[1063,1111,676,702]" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="9DF31AB1FFAF983105A9AEF976A5FD6C" authorityName="Samsinak" authorityYear="1958" box="[1273,1408,675,702]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Hypoaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helianthi">
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF983105A9AEF97628FD6C" box="[1273,1293,676,701]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF9831044CAEFE76A5FD6C" box="[1308,1408,675,701]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">helianthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in order to confirm that synonymy, but by comparing the descriptions and figures of these two species, we found some distinguishing morphological differences: (1) sternal seta 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF9831024DAEB6701BFCD4" box="[797,830,747,773]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">st1</emphasis>
is off the sternal shield in 
<taxonomicName id="9DF31AB1FFAF98310536AEB177C9FCD4" authorityName="Samsinak" authorityYear="1958" box="[1126,1260,747,774]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Hypoaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helianthi">
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF98310536AEB1775FFCD4" box="[1126,1146,748,773]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF983105D8AEB677C9FCD4" box="[1160,1260,747,773]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">helianthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<figureCitation id="C2C87DB7FFAF98310477AEB676B8FCD4" box="[1319,1437,747,773]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[182,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. DIC micrographs of Cosmolaelaps chianensis (Gu), female. 1, idiosoma in dorsal view, enlarged section not to scale; 2, idiosoma in ventral view; 3, sternal shield; 4, general view of opisthogastric area; 5, chelicera; 6, dorsal aspect of femur, genu and tibia leg I; 7, ventral aspect of femur, genu and tibia leg I." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530960" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530960/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">
Figure 4- 
<quantity id="9D0BCCD7FFAF983104C2AEB676B8FCD4" box="[1426,1437,747,773]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" unit="in" value="1.0">1</quantity>
</figureCitation>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="3E621CC3FFAF983101E5AF52724EFCFB" author="Samsinak, K." box="[181,363,783,810]" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" pagination="185 - 198" refId="ref16440" refString="Samsinak, K. (1958) Roztoci ze slunecnicovych semen (Acari). Ceskoslovenska Parasitologie, 5, 185 - 198. [in Czech]" type="journal article" year="1958">Samšiňák, 1958</bibRefCitation>
), while in 
<taxonomicName id="9DF31AB1FFAF983100B4AF4D715BFCF8" baseAuthorityName="Shcherbak" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[484,638,783,810]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Cosmolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lutegiensis">
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF983100B4AF4D72D2FCFB" box="[484,503,784,810]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF98310356AF52715BFCF8" box="[518,638,783,809]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">lutegiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is obviously on the shield (see 
<figureCitation id="C2C87DB7FFAF983102ABAF52776EFCF8" box="[1019,1099,783,809]" captionStart="FIGURE 21–24" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1926,1950]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,197,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[152,1436,181,1902]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 21–24. Cosmolaelaps lasiophilus Joharchi sp. nov., female. 21, leg I (trochanter-tibia); 22, leg II; 23, leg III; 24, leg IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530972" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530972/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">
Fig. 
<quantity id="9D0BCCD7FFAF9831057FAF52776EFCF8" box="[1071,1099,783,809]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.334" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" unit="in" value="21.0">21</quantity>
</figureCitation>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="3E621CC3FFAF98310520AF52764DFCF8" author="Joharchi, O. &amp; Issakova, A. K. &amp; Asyamova, O. S. &amp; Abbasi-Sarcheshmeh, M. &amp; Tolstikov, A. V." box="[1136,1384,783,810]" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" pagination="473 - 498" refId="ref14853" refString="Joharchi, O., Issakova, A. K., Asyamova, O. S., Abbasi-Sarcheshmeh, M. &amp; Tolstikov, A. V. (2020 a) Some soil-inhabiting mites (Acari: Mesostigmata) from Kazakhstan, with description of a new species of Gaeolaelaps Evans &amp; Till (Acari: Laelapidae). Zootaxa, 4819 (3), 473 - 498. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4819.3.3" type="journal article" year="2020">
Joharchi 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF98310587AF4D762CFCF8" box="[1239,1289,783,809]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">et al</emphasis>
., 2020a
</bibRefCitation>
); (2) dorsal setae smooth and mostly do not reach to base of next setae in series (see 
<figureCitation id="C2C87DB7FFAF98310550AF6E7751FC9F" box="[1024,1140,819,846]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[182,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. DIC micrographs of Cosmolaelaps chianensis (Gu), female. 1, idiosoma in dorsal view, enlarged section not to scale; 2, idiosoma in ventral view; 3, sternal shield; 4, general view of opisthogastric area; 5, chelicera; 6, dorsal aspect of femur, genu and tibia leg I; 7, ventral aspect of femur, genu and tibia leg I." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530960" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530960/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">
Figure 5- 
<quantity id="9D0BCCD7FFAF98310539AF6E7751FC9F" box="[1129,1140,819,846]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" unit="in" value="1.0">1</quantity>
</figureCitation>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="3E621CC3FFAF983105C6AF6E766EFC9F" author="Samsinak, K." box="[1174,1355,819,846]" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" pagination="185 - 198" refId="ref16440" refString="Samsinak, K. (1958) Roztoci ze slunecnicovych semen (Acari). Ceskoslovenska Parasitologie, 5, 185 - 198. [in Czech]" type="journal article" year="1958">Samšiňák, 1958</bibRefCitation>
), while in 
<taxonomicName id="9DF31AB1FFAF983101E5AF05726AFCA0" baseAuthorityName="Shcherbak" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[181,335,855,882]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Cosmolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lutegiensis">
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF983101E5AF0573EDFCA3" box="[181,200,856,882]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF98310187AF0A726AFCA0" box="[215,335,855,881]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">lutegiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
all setae have a small basal protuberance and are mostly long enough to reach base of next setae in series (see 
<figureCitation id="C2C87DB7FFAF98310062AF267288FC44" box="[306,429,891,917]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–20" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[198,1388,181,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[198,1389,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13–20. DIC micrographs of Cosmolaelaps lasiophilus Joharchi sp. nov., female. 13, idiosoma in dorsal view; 14, idiosoma in ventral view; 15, general view of some podonotal setae; 16, general view of some opisthonotal setae; 17, general view of part of opisthogastric area; 18, subcapitulum; 19, distal portion of palp, with focus on tarsal claw; 20, insemination structures." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530968" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530968/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">
Figures 
<quantity id="9D0BCCD7FFAF983100DEAF267288FC44" box="[398,429,891,917]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.135879999999999" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" unit="in" value="20.22">20</quantity>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C2C87DB7FFAF983100E9AF2672F0FC44" box="[441,469,891,917]" captionStart="FIGURE 21–24" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1926,1950]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,197,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[152,1436,181,1902]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 21–24. Cosmolaelaps lasiophilus Joharchi sp. nov., female. 21, leg I (trochanter-tibia); 22, leg II; 23, leg III; 24, leg IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530972" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530972/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">22</figureCitation>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="3E621CC3FFAF983100ABAF2671D6FC44" author="Joharchi, O. &amp; Issakova, A. K. &amp; Asyamova, O. S. &amp; Abbasi-Sarcheshmeh, M. &amp; Tolstikov, A. V." box="[507,755,891,918]" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" pagination="473 - 498" refId="ref14853" refString="Joharchi, O., Issakova, A. K., Asyamova, O. S., Abbasi-Sarcheshmeh, M. &amp; Tolstikov, A. V. (2020 a) Some soil-inhabiting mites (Acari: Mesostigmata) from Kazakhstan, with description of a new species of Gaeolaelaps Evans &amp; Till (Acari: Laelapidae). Zootaxa, 4819 (3), 473 - 498. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4819.3.3" type="journal article" year="2020">
Joharchi 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF98310332AF2171B1FC44" box="[610,660,891,917]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">et al</emphasis>
., 2020a
</bibRefCitation>
); (3) sternal shield with reticulate ornamentation throughout 
<taxonomicName id="9DF31AB1FFAF983101C7AFFD723AFC68" authorityName="Samsinak" authorityYear="1958" box="[151,287,927,954]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Hypoaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helianthi">
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF983101C7AFFD738EFC68" box="[151,171,928,953]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF983101EBAFC2723AFC68" box="[187,287,927,953]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">helianthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<figureCitation id="C2C87DB7FFAF9831000DAFC272F1FC68" box="[349,468,927,953]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[182,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. DIC micrographs of Cosmolaelaps chianensis (Gu), female. 1, idiosoma in dorsal view, enlarged section not to scale; 2, idiosoma in ventral view; 3, sternal shield; 4, general view of opisthogastric area; 5, chelicera; 6, dorsal aspect of femur, genu and tibia leg I; 7, ventral aspect of femur, genu and tibia leg I." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530960" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530960/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">
Figure 4- 
<quantity id="9D0BCCD7FFAF98310099AFC272F1FC68" box="[457,468,927,953]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" unit="in" value="1.0">1</quantity>
</figureCitation>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="3E621CC3FFAF983100AAAFC27197FC6B" author="Samsinak, K." box="[506,690,927,954]" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" pagination="185 - 198" refId="ref16440" refString="Samsinak, K. (1958) Roztoci ze slunecnicovych semen (Acari). Ceskoslovenska Parasitologie, 5, 185 - 198. [in Czech]" type="journal article" year="1958">Samšiňák, 1958</bibRefCitation>
), while in 
<taxonomicName id="9DF31AB1FFAF9831027DAFFD70E2FC68" baseAuthorityName="Shcherbak" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[813,967,927,954]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Cosmolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lutegiensis">
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF9831027DAFFD7065FC6B" box="[813,832,928,954]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF9831021FAFC270E2FC68" box="[847,967,927,953]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">lutegiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shield smooth almost throughout, except a longitudinally lateral part between 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF98310365AF9E7172FC0C" box="[565,599,963,989]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">iv1</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF983103DEAF9E718AFC0C" box="[654,687,963,989]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">st3</emphasis>
faintly reticulated with curved lines (see 
<figureCitation id="C2C87DB7FFAF983105D2AF9E77F7FC0C" box="[1154,1234,963,989]" captionStart="FIGURE 21–24" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1926,1950]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,197,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[152,1436,181,1902]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 21–24. Cosmolaelaps lasiophilus Joharchi sp. nov., female. 21, leg I (trochanter-tibia); 22, leg II; 23, leg III; 24, leg IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530972" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530972/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">
Fig. 
<quantity id="9D0BCCD7FFAF983105E6AF9E77F7FC0C" box="[1206,1234,963,989]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.334" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" unit="in" value="21.0">21</quantity>
</figureCitation>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="3E621CC3FFAF983105A6AF9E73C4FBD0" author="Joharchi, O. &amp; Issakova, A. K. &amp; Asyamova, O. S. &amp; Abbasi-Sarcheshmeh, M. &amp; Tolstikov, A. V." pageId="15" pageNumber="501" pagination="473 - 498" refId="ref14853" refString="Joharchi, O., Issakova, A. K., Asyamova, O. S., Abbasi-Sarcheshmeh, M. &amp; Tolstikov, A. V. (2020 a) Some soil-inhabiting mites (Acari: Mesostigmata) from Kazakhstan, with description of a new species of Gaeolaelaps Evans &amp; Till (Acari: Laelapidae). Zootaxa, 4819 (3), 473 - 498. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4819.3.3" type="journal article" year="2020">
Joharchi 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF9831040DAF9976ABFC0C" box="[1373,1422,963,989]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">et al</emphasis>
., 2020a
</bibRefCitation>
). Therefore, we believe these are two distinct species.
</paragraph>
